# Plan Gate Review — MN State Park Tracker

## Findings

Plan status: **READY** (planner confirms all blockers resolved post-research). Verified complete:

- All 8 posting requirements traced to concrete components, routes, and files
- Architecture fully specified: Vite+React frontend + Flask blueprint + 4 isolated SQLite tables
- All API routes defined with auth requirements (JWT, demo account seeded `demo@mnparks.test` / `Parks2024!`)
- Design system: specific hex tokens, Playfair Display + Inter, MN official brand palette
- Data strategy: ArcGIS REST primary + hand-curated lat/lng fallback both planned
- Photo upload: client-side canvas resize (1200px / JPEG 0.75) + waitress body limit fix planned
- File budget: 2 deployed files (well under 12)
- Two-way map/list sync, distance from home, visit history all scoped to components
- Previous blockers resolved: park data source confirmed (ArcGIS REST endpoint URL in plan); Maps API key absent → Leaflet + CartoDB Voyager committed as primary (functionally equivalent)

**Open items (build-time only, mitigations in place):**
- ArcGIS endpoint live test at build time → fallback hand-curated array ready in demo-builder brief
- Park description curation (~75 parks) → tractable, demo-builder task
- Waitress `max_request_body_size` → must be set before photo upload test

No gaps requiring additional research.

## Problems

None.

